The paper discusses a natural language interface (NLI) to databases, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the spatial domain, which involves spatial data and spatial queries, indicating a connection to databases (cs.DB). The proposed spatial comprehension model is based on machine learning techniques, such as deep learning and neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) tasks, such as translating natural language questions to executable queries, which is another indication of the relevance to cs.IR.
